HEADWORD: Spindle-shaped
<hw>Spin"dle-shaped`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Having the shape of a spindle.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>Thickest in the middle, and
tapering to both ends; fusiform; -- applied chiefly to roots.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Spindletail</ent>⟦br⟧
